(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 this title or objects to the issuance of a license or permit by
2 filing an objection pursuant to Section 6-103.1 of this title;
3 3. Any person whose driving privilege has been suspended,
4 revoked, canceled, or denied in this state or any other state or
5 country until the driving privilege has been reinstated by the state
6 or country withdrawing the privilege;
7 4. Any person who is classified as an excessive user of
8 alcohol, any other intoxicating substance, or a combination of
9 alcohol and any other intoxicating substance, and inimical to public
10 safety, in accordance with rules promulgated by the Department
11 Service Oklahoma, until all requirements granting or reinstating
12 driving privileges are met, including, but not limited to,
13 abstinence from the use of alcohol, any other intoxicating
14 substance, or any combination of alcohol and any other intoxicating
15 substance for a minimum of either twelve (12) months or eighteen
16 (18) months, as determined by OAC 595:10-5 670:15-11-11, immediately
17 preceding application for or application for reinstatement of
18 driving privileges;
19 5. Any person who is required by Section 6-101 et seq. of this
20 title to take an examination, unless the person shall have
21 successfully passed the examination;
22 6. Any person who is required under the laws of this state to
23 deposit proof of financial responsibility and who has not deposited
24 such proof;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2010 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 7. Any person who is physically deformed or who is afflicted
2 with any mental disease or physical condition that would impair the
3 driving ability of the person or when the Commissioner of Public
4 Safety, from information concerning the person or from the records
5 and reports on file in the Department of Public Safety, determines
6 that the operation of a motor vehicle by such person on the highways
7 would be inimical to public safety or welfare;
8 8. Any person who is a nonresident, as defined in Section 1-137
9 of this title;
10 9. Any alien noncitizen, unless such person presents valid
11 documentation of identity and authorization for presence in the
12 United States issued pursuant to the laws of the United States;
13 provided, no license shall be issued to any alien noncitizen whose
14 documentation indicates the alien noncitizen is a visitor or is not
15 eligible to establish residency; or
16 10. Any person who possesses a valid license to operate a motor
17 vehicle issued by another state until the other state license has
18 been surrendered.
19 B. Any applicant who is denied a license under the provisions
20 of subsection A of this section shall have the right to an appeal as
21 provided in Section 6-211 of this title.
22 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-106, as
23 last amended by Section 5, Chapter 11, O.S.L. 2024 (47 O.S. Supp.
24 2025, Section 6-106), is amended to read as follows:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2010 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Section 6-106. A. 1. Every application for a driver license
2 or identification card shall be made by the applicant upon a form
3 furnished by Service Oklahoma.
4 2. Every original, renewal, or replacement application for a
5 driver license or identification card made by a male applicant who
6 is at least sixteen (16) but less than twenty-six (26) years of age
7 shall include a statement that by submitting the application, the
8 applicant is consenting to registration with the Selective Service
9 System. The pertinent information from the application shall be
10 forwarded by Service Oklahoma to the Data Management Center of the
11 Selective Service System in order to register the applicant as
12 required by law with the Selective Service System. Any applicant
13 refusing to sign the consent statement shall be denied a driver
14 license or identification card.
15 3. Except as provided for in subsections G and, H, and I of
16 this section, every applicant for a driver license or identification
17 card shall provide to Service Oklahoma at the time of application a
18 document showing proof of identity. Service Oklahoma shall
19 promulgate rules prescribing forms of identification acceptable for
20 an original Oklahoma driver license.
21 B. Every applicant for a driver license shall provide the
22 following information:
23 1. Full name;
24 2. Date of birth;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2010 SFLR Page 4
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 3. Sex;
2 4. Address of principal residence and county of such residence,
3 which shall be referenced on the REAL ID Compliant Driver License or
4 Identification Card;, and proof of such principal residency, as
5 prescribed by rules promulgated by Service Oklahoma, documenting
6 provided address;
7 5. Current and complete mailing address to be maintained by
8 Service Oklahoma for the purpose of giving notice, if necessary, as
9 required by Section 2-116 of this title;
10 6. Medical information, as determined by the Department of
11 Public Safety, which shall assure Service Oklahoma that the person
12 is not prohibited from being licensed as provided by paragraph 7 of
13 subsection A of Section 6-103 of this title;
14 7. Whether the applicant is deaf or hard-of-hearing;
15 8. A brief description of the applicant, as determined by the
16 Department;
17 9. Whether the applicant has previously been licensed, and, if
18 so, when and by what state or country, and whether any license has
19 ever been suspended or revoked, or whether an application has ever
20 been refused, and, if so, the date of and reason for the suspension,
21 revocation, or refusal;
22 10. Whether the applicant is an alien a noncitizen eligible to
23 be considered for licensure and is not prohibited from licensure
