12 2. If the applicant is applying for an original commercial
13 driver license in Oklahoma or is transferring a commercial driver
14 license from another state to Oklahoma, Service Oklahoma shall
15 review the driving record of the applicant in other states for the
16 immediately preceding ten (10) years, unless the record review has
17 already been performed by Service Oklahoma. As a result of the
18 review, if it is determined by Service Oklahoma that the applicant
19 is subject to a period of disqualification as prescribed by Section
20 6-205.2 of this title which has not yet been imposed, Service
21 Oklahoma shall impose the period of disqualification and the
22 applicant shall serve the period of disqualification before a
23 commercial driver license is issued to the applicant; provided,
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2010 SFLR Page 7
