1 noth ing in this paragraph shall be construed to prevent the issuance
2 of a Class D driver license to the applicant.
3 3. If the applicant has or is applying for a hazardous material
4 endorsement, the applicant shall submit to a security threat
5 assessment performed by the Transportation Security Administration
6 of the Department of Homeland Security as required by and pursuant
7 to 49 C.F.R., Part 1572, which shall be used to determine whether
