3 H. A valid and unexpired U.S. passport shall serve as both
4 primary and secondary proofs of identity whenever application for a
5 driver license or identification card is submitted to the
6 Department. Service Oklahoma shall promulgate rules necessary to
7 implement and administer the provisions of this subsection.
8 I. As provided in Section 6-103 of this title, any applicant
9 who is a noncitizen shall present a valid proof of lawful presence,
10 which may serve as a primary proof of identity, whenever application
11 or renewal for a driver license or identification card is submitted
12 to the Department. Service Oklahoma shall promulgate rules
13 necessary to implement and administer the provisions of this
14 subsection.
15 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-111.1 of Title 47, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. 1. Any noncitizen applying for an original, renewal, or
19 replacement REAL ID Compliant Driver License or Identification Card
20 shall be issued a license or card bearing the words “Limited Term”.
21 2. On or before July 1, 2027, and annually thereafter, Service
22 Oklahoma shall electronically report to the Governor, the President
23 Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2010 SFLR Page 10
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 Repr esentatives the number of licenses or cards bearing the words
2 “Limited Term” that have been issued in this state.
3 B. 1. Any noncitizen applying for an original, renewal, or
4 replacement REAL ID Noncompliant Driver License or Identification
5 Card shall be issued a license or card bearing the words “Federal
6 Limits Apply”.
7 2. On or before July 1, 2027, and annually thereafter, Service
8 Oklahoma shall electronically report to the Governor, the President
9 Pro Tempore of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of
10 Representatives the number of licenses or cards bearing the words
11 “Federal Limits Apply” that have been issued in this state.
12 C. Service Oklahoma shall promulgate rules necessary to
13 implement and administer the provisions of this section.
